/F2 15 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 732.0 Tm (Error and Honesty in the Waggle Dance: How Recruitment Tolerates Imprecise Distance Signals) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 718.0 Tm () Tj
/F1 9 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 704.0 Tm (Friedrich Maas and Lena Soto) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 690.0 Tm (Insect Behaviour and Communication, Vol. 11, No. 4 \(1983\) - JID-009) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 676.0 Tm () Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 658.0 Tm (Abstract) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 644.0 Tm (The honeybee waggle dance encodes the direction and distance of a resource, yet individual) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 630.0 Tm (dances are noticeably imprecise. By filming and decoding several hundred dances and tracking) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 616.0 Tm (the recruits they produced, we quantify the scatter in distance signalling and show that) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 602.0 Tm (recruitment success is surprisingly robust to it. We propose that the imprecision is not a) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 588.0 Tm (flaw but a feature that spreads recruits across a foraging zone rather than concentrating) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 574.0 Tm (them at a single point.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 560.0 Tm () Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 542.0 Tm (Introduction) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 528.0 Tm (When a forager honeybee returns from a productive flower patch, she performs a looping dance) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 514.0 Tm (on the comb whose straight 'waggle' run encodes the direction of the patch relative to the) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 500.0 Tm (sun and, through its duration, the distance to it. The elegance of this system has made it a) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 486.0 Tm (textbook example of animal communication.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 472.0 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 56 458.0 Tm (Less often discussed is how imprecise individual dances are. Repeated dances for the same) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 444.0 Tm (source vary in their encoded distance by a wide margin. This study asks whether that scatter) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 430.0 Tm (degrades recruitment, as one would naively expect, or whether the colony tolerates and) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 416.0 Tm (perhaps exploits it.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 402.0 Tm () Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 384.0 Tm (Filming and Decoding) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 370.0 Tm (We trained foragers to feeders at known distances and filmed their dances on an observation) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 356.0 Tm (hive through a glass wall. Each waggle run was timed frame by frame, and the encoded) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 342.0 Tm (distance was read from run duration using a calibration established for our colony.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 328.0 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 56 314.0 Tm (Recruits were tracked by marking dance followers and recording where they subsequently) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 300.0 Tm (appeared along a line of monitored feeders. This let us compare the distance a dance encoded) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 286.0 Tm (with the distances at which its followers actually searched.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 272.0 Tm () Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 254.0 Tm (Quantifying the Scatter) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 240.0 Tm (Dances for a single feeder produced a broad distribution of encoded distances, far broader) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 226.0 Tm (than the precision of our timing could explain. The scatter grew with distance, so that) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 212.0 Tm (dances for far sources were proportionally vaguer than those for near ones.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 198.0 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 56 184.0 Tm (Strikingly, recruitment did not collapse under this vagueness. Followers fanned out across a) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 170.0 Tm (band of distances centred near the true source, and the colony reliably exploited the feeder) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 156.0 Tm (despite no single dance pointing to it precisely. The signal was noisy, but the collective) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 142.0 Tm (response was sound.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 128.0 Tm () Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 110.0 Tm (Imprecision as Strategy) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 96.0 Tm (We argue that the scatter is adaptive. A real flower patch is not a point but an area, and) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 82.0 Tm (recruits spread across a band of distances are more likely to discover its full extent than) Tj
